<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Coach the Moment — IPR</title>
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Fraunces:ital,opsz,wght@0,9..144,400;0,9..144,600;0,9..144,800;1,9..144,500&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
  :root {
    --lime: #c8e830;
    --lime-deep: #a8c424;
    --lime-soft: #f0f8d4;
    --ink: #0f1410;
    --ink-soft: #2a302a;
    --paper: #fdfdf8;
    --paper-shadow: #e8e8df;
    --rule: #1a1e1a;
    --muted: #6b706b;
    --red: #c84b3a;
    --amber: #d4941e;
    --green: #3d8b52;
  }

  * {
    box-sizing: border-box;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
  }

  body {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', Georgia, serif;
    background: var(--paper);
    color: var(--ink);
    line-height: 1.5;
    padding: 0;
    min-height: 100vh;
    background-image:
      radial-gradient(circle at 20% 10%, rgba(200, 232, 48, 0.08) 0%, transparent 40%),
      radial-gradient(circle at 80% 90%, rgba(200, 232, 48, 0.06) 0%, transparent 40%);
  }

  .container {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 48px 28px 80px;
  }

  /* ============ HEADER ============ */
  .header {
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--ink);
    padding-bottom: 24px;
    margin-bottom: 32px;
    position: relative;
  }

  .eyebrow {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink);
    background: var(--lime);
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 5px 10px 4px;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  h1 {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
    font-weight: 800;
    font-size: clamp(30px, 5vw, 44px);
    line-height: 1.05;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }

  h1 em {
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
  }

  .subtitle {
    font-size: 16px;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 400;
  }

  /* ============ SCENARIO TRACKER ============ */
  .tracker {
    display: flex;
    gap: 6px;
    margin-bottom: 28px;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .tracker-label {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin-right: 10px;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .tracker-pips {
    display: flex;
    gap: 6px;
    flex: 1;
  }

  .pip {
    width: 28px;
    height: 4px;
    background: var(--paper-shadow);
    transition: background 0.3s ease;
  }

  .pip.active {
    background: var(--ink);
  }

  .pip.complete {
    background: var(--lime-deep);
  }

  .tracker-count {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    margin-left: 10px;
  }

  /* ============ STAGE LABEL ============ */
  .stage-label {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 14px;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin-bottom: 18px;
  }

  .stage-label .dot {
    width: 8px;
    height: 8px;
    background: var(--lime);
    border-radius: 50%;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px var(--lime-soft);
  }

  .stage-label .line {
    flex: 1;
    height: 1px;
    background: var(--rule);
    opacity: 0.2;
  }

  .stage-label .scenario-tag {
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--ink);
  }

  /* ============ SCENARIO CARD ============ */
  .scenario {
    background: var(--ink);
    color: var(--paper);
    padding: 32px 30px;
    border-radius: 2px;
    position: relative;
    margin-bottom: 28px;
    box-shadow: 8px 8px 0 var(--lime);
  }

  .scenario::before {
    content: attr(data-label);
    position: absolute;
    top: -10px;
    left: 24px;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    font-weight: 700;
    background: var(--lime);
    color: var(--ink);
    padding: 4px 10px;
  }

  .scenario-title {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 15px;
    color: var(--lime);
    margin-bottom: 14px;
    letter-spacing: 0.01em;
  }

  .scenario-text {
    font-size: 18px;
    line-height: 1.55;
    font-weight: 400;
  }

  .scenario-text strong {
    font-weight: 600;
    background: linear-gradient(transparent 65%, rgba(200, 232, 48, 0.35) 65%);
    padding: 0 2px;
  }

  .scenario-text em {
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .time-pressure {
    margin-top: 18px;
    padding-top: 18px;
    border-top: 1px dashed rgba(253, 253, 248, 0.2);
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 12px;
    color: var(--lime);
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  /* ============ PROMPT ============ */
  .prompt {
    text-align: center;
    margin: 32px 0 20px;
  }

  .prompt-text {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 21px;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--ink);
  }

  /* ============ CHOICES ============ */
  .choices {
    display: grid;
    gap: 12px;
    margin-bottom: 28px;
  }

  .choice {
    background: var(--paper);
    border: 2px solid var(--ink);
    padding: 16px 20px;
    text-align: left;
    font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.4;
    color: var(--ink);
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all 0.2s ease;
    position: relative;
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 14px;
    width: 100%;
    font-weight: 400;
  }

  .choice:hover:not(:disabled) {
    background: var(--lime-soft);
    transform: translate(-2px, -2px);
    box-shadow: 4px 4px 0 var(--ink);
  }

  .choice:active:not(:disabled) {
    transform: translate(0, 0);
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 var(--ink);
  }

  .choice-letter {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 13px;
    background: var(--ink);
    color: var(--paper);
    width: 26px;
    height: 26px;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    margin-top: 1px;
  }

  .choice:disabled {
    cursor: default;
    opacity: 0.35;
  }

  .choice.selected {
    background: var(--lime);
    border-color: var(--ink);
    opacity: 1 !important;
  }

  .choice.selected .choice-letter {
    background: var(--paper);
    color: var(--ink);
  }

  /* ============ FEEDBACK PANEL ============ */
  .feedback {
    display: none;
    margin-top: 28px;
    animation: slideIn 0.4s ease-out;
  }

  .feedback.visible {
    display: block;
  }

  @keyframes slideIn {
    from {
      opacity: 0;
      transform: translateY(12px);
    }
    to {
      opacity: 1;
      transform: translateY(0);
    }
  }

  .verdict {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 12px;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    font-weight: 700;
    padding: 10px 16px;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
    width: fit-content;
  }

  .verdict.inr {
    background: var(--red);
    color: var(--paper);
  }

  .verdict.mixed {
    background: var(--amber);
    color: var(--paper);
  }

  .verdict.ipr {
    background: var(--green);
    color: var(--paper);
  }

  .feedback-body {
    background: var(--paper);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--ink);
    padding: 4px 0 4px 22px;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }

  .feedback-label {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin-bottom: 6px;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .feedback-text {
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .feedback-text:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .feedback-text em {
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .danielle-says {
    background: var(--lime-soft);
    border: 1px solid var(--lime-deep);
    padding: 22px 24px;
    position: relative;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }

  .danielle-says::before {
    content: 'WHAT I’D DO';
    position: absolute;
    top: -9px;
    left: 16px;
    background: var(--paper);
    padding: 0 8px;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--ink);
  }

  .danielle-says p {
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--ink);
  }

  .danielle-says p + p {
    margin-top: 10px;
  }

  .danielle-says strong {
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  /* ============ CONTROLS ============ */
  .controls {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
    margin-top: 28px;
    padding-top: 24px;
    border-top: 1px dashed var(--rule);
    opacity: 0.5;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .controls.visible {
    opacity: 1;
  }

  .btn {
    background: none;
    border: 1px solid var(--ink);
    padding: 10px 18px;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink);
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all 0.15s ease;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .btn:hover:not(:disabled) {
    background: var(--ink);
    color: var(--paper);
  }

  .btn:disabled {
    opacity: 0.3;
    cursor: default;
  }

  .btn.primary {
    background: var(--ink);
    color: var(--paper);
  }

  .btn.primary:hover {
    background: var(--lime);
    color: var(--ink);
    border-color: var(--ink);
  }

  /* ============ COMPLETION CARD ============ */
  .completion {
    display: none;
    background: var(--ink);
    color: var(--paper);
    padding: 40px 32px;
    text-align: center;
    margin-top: 32px;
    box-shadow: 8px 8px 0 var(--lime);
    animation: slideIn 0.5s ease-out;
  }

  .completion.visible {
    display: block;
  }

  .completion-eyebrow {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    color: var(--lime);
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 14px;
  }

  .completion h2 {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', serif;
    font-weight: 800;
    font-size: 28px;
    line-height: 1.15;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  .completion h2 em {
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--lime);
  }

  .completion p {
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--paper);
    opacity: 0.88;
    max-width: 520px;
    margin: 0 auto 20px;
  }

  .completion .restart {
    margin-top: 12px;
    background: var(--lime);
    color: var(--ink);
    border: none;
    padding: 12px 24px;
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    font-weight: 700;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all 0.15s ease;
  }

  .completion .restart:hover {
    background: var(--paper);
  }

  /* ============ FOOTER ============ */
  .footer-note {
    margin-top: 48px;
    padding-top: 28px;
    border-top: 2px solid var(--ink);
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--muted);
    line-height: 1.55;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .footer-note strong {
    font-style: normal;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--ink);
  }

  /* ============ RESPONSIVE ============ */
  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .container {
      padding: 32px 18px 60px;
    }
    .scenario {
      padding: 26px 20px;
      box-shadow: 6px 6px 0 var(--lime);
    }
    .scenario-text {
      font-size: 16px;
    }
    .choice {
      font-size: 15px;
      padding: 14px 16px;
    }
    .prompt-text {
      font-size: 18px;
    }
    .pip {
      width: 20px;
    }
    .controls {
      justify-content: center;
    }
    .completion {
      padding: 32px 22px;
      box-shadow: 6px 6px 0 var(--lime);
    }
    .completion h2 {
      font-size: 24px;
    }
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="container">

  <header class="header">
    <div class="eyebrow">Coach the Moment · IPR</div>
    <h1>Two seconds. <em>One choice.</em></h1>
    <p class="subtitle">Five coaching scenarios on Instant Positive Response.</p>
  </header>

  <div class="tracker">
    <span class="tracker-label">Scenarios</span>
    <div class="tracker-pips" id="trackerPips"></div>
    <span class="tracker-count" id="trackerCount">1 / 5</span>
  </div>

  <div id="scenarioView">
    <!-- Scenario content injected here -->
  </div>

  <div class="completion" id="completion">
    <div class="completion-eyebrow">LAB COMPLETE</div>
    <h2>Nice work. <em>Five moments, one habit.</em></h2>
    <p>
      IPR isn't a single choice — it's a pattern you build across seasons. The coach
      your athletes remember is the one who shows them how to reset faster than they
      could on their own.
    </p>
    <p>
      Run through the scenarios again. Try the answers you didn't pick the first
      time. Notice which ones felt obvious and which ones you had to think about —
      that's your growing edge.
    </p>
    <button class="restart" id="restartBtn">↻ Run it again</button>
  </div>

  <div class="footer-note">
    <strong>Why this exercise?</strong> Most coaching decisions happen in the two
    seconds between a mistake and the next play. Reading about IPR is easy. Choosing
    it under time pressure is the whole skill. Come back as many times as you need.
  </div>

</div>

<script>
  const scenarios = [
    {
      id: 1,
      label: 'THE MOMENT',
      title: 'The visible frustration',
      text: 'Your player just had a <strong>bad trap</strong> in a 2v2. The ball rolls out of bounds. She slams her stick down and mouths <em>"sorry"</em> with her head hanging.',
      timing: '▸ You have ~2 seconds before the next restart.',
      choices: [
        {
          key: 'A',
          text: 'Call her over and talk about what went wrong with the trap.',
          verdict: 'INR',
          verdictClass: 'inr',
          verdictLabel: 'Reinforces Instant Negative Response',
          analysis: [
            "Pulling her over mid-drill sends three signals at once: <em>the mistake was big enough to stop play</em>, <em>the way you're already feeling about it is the right way to feel</em>, and <em>we're going to sit in it for a minute</em>. All three reinforce INR.",
            "There's a time to teach the trap. It isn't here. When you stop play to talk about a mistake, you've just taught every player on the field that mistakes are things we stop for — not things we move past."
          ],
          danielle: [
            "Teaching moments land better when they're <strong>separated from the emotional moment</strong>. If her trap needs work, I'll cue it at the next water break — or work it into the drill design next week. Not in the 2 seconds after she's already embarrassed."
          ]
        },
        {
          key: 'B',
          text: 'Say nothing. Let her work through it on her own.',
          verdict: 'Mixed',
          verdictClass: 'mixed',
          verdictLabel: "Neutral — and neutral isn't enough",
          analysis: [
            "This isn't wrong. Silence protects you from overcoaching, and some athletes genuinely need space to reset on their own.",
            "But IPR is a <em>trained</em> skill, not a default one. If she could already reset on her own, she would have. Right now she's carrying the bowl — and nobody's shown her the strainer. Silence here leaves her alone with the mistake."
          ],
          danielle: [
            "Silence is a tool I use when an athlete has <strong>already shown me she can IPR</strong>. Then stepping back is respect. Early in the season — or with an athlete who just slammed her stick — silence reads as absence, not trust."
          ]
        },
        {
          key: 'C',
          text: 'Make eye contact, point at your head, and clap.',
          verdict: 'IPR',
          verdictClass: 'ipr',
          verdictLabel: 'Strong Execute move',
          analysis: [
            "Eye contact + point to the head + clap does three things in under a second: it <em>names the behavior</em> (reset your mind), <em>affirms her</em> (I see you, I'm with you), and <em>keeps play moving</em> (we don't stop for this).",
            "Zero words. Zero interruption. Pure coaching."
          ],
          danielle: [
            "This is the one I'd pick nine times out of ten. The clap is the part most coaches miss — it turns a correction into a <strong>connection</strong>. Point-and-clap reads as <em>get your head back, and I've got you</em>."
          ]
        },
        {
          key: 'D',
          text: 'Call out "strainer!" and keep play moving.',
          verdict: 'IPR',
          verdictClass: 'ipr',
          verdictLabel: 'Strong Execute move — if the language is shared',
          analysis: [
            "Using <em>\"strainer!\"</em> as a live cue is exactly the payoff of the Bowl vs. Strainer analogy — one word that carries the whole concept. The mental frame activates instantly and play continues.",
            "This only works if you've already laid the groundwork. If the team doesn't know the analogy yet, \"strainer\" is just a strange word yelled at a kid who's already embarrassed."
          ],
          danielle: [
            "I love a shared vocabulary cue. <em>Strainer</em>, <em>POP</em>, <em>triple threat</em> — these let me coach in one syllable from 30 yards away. But the cue is only as strong as the concept behind it. <strong>Teach the analogy first. Then the word does the work.</strong>"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      id: 2,
      label: 'THE MOMENT',
      title: 'Snapping at a teammate',
      text: 'In a 3v3, your center made a bad pass and your wing snaps: <em>"Oh my god, what was that?!"</em> The center freezes. The wing is still glaring. <strong>Play is about to restart.</strong>',
      timing: '▸ 2 seconds. Both players are watching you now.',
      choices: [
        {
          key: 'A',
          text: 'Stop play and address the wing\'s comment directly.',
          verdict: 'Mixed',
          verdictClass: 'mixed',
          verdictLabel: 'Right intent, wrong moment',
          analysis: [
            "The wing's behavior absolutely needs addressing — but stopping play to do it <em>in front of everyone</em> turns a coaching moment into public discipline. The wing shuts down. The center feels exposed.",
            "Worse: you've just spent 30 seconds on a conversation that could've happened in a 60-second water break with more care."
          ],
          danielle: [
            "I never stop a drill to call out a player's attitude in front of the group. If I can coach it <em>through</em> the drill, I do. If I can't, it waits — and I pull the wing aside at the next natural break. <strong>Discipline happens in private. Culture happens in public.</strong>"
          ]
        },
        {
          key: 'B',
          text: 'Ignore it. Focus on the next play.',
          verdict: 'INR',
          verdictClass: 'inr',
          verdictLabel: 'Silence = permission',
          analysis: [
            "Coaches sometimes think staying out of teammate conflict respects the athletes' autonomy. In practice, it signals that snapping at a teammate after a mistake is acceptable — because nobody corrected it.",
            "Your job isn't to referee every small comment. But this one was loud enough that the center froze. That means every other player on the field saw it too. If you ignore it, <em>the team learns the wrong lesson</em>."
          ],
          danielle: [
            "I'm watching for team IPR, not just individual IPR. A teammate who <em>adds</em> to another player's mistake is carrying the bowl <em>and</em> pouring water into their teammate's. That gets named. Quietly. Quickly. Always."
          ]
        },
        {
          key: 'C',
          text: 'As play restarts, call to the wing: "That\'s on you — go get her next play."',
          verdict: 'IPR',
          verdictClass: 'ipr',
          verdictLabel: 'Redirects ownership without stopping play',
          analysis: [
            "This does a lot in one sentence. It names that the wing's reaction — not the pass — was the actual problem (<em>\"that's on you\"</em>). It gives her something to do with her energy (<em>\"go get her\"</em>). And it models IPR in real time: mistake → cue → move on.",
            "You've also, subtly, told the center: <em>I see what just happened. You're not alone.</em>"
          ],
          danielle: [
            "This is Liberty's Failure Recovery System, but applied to <em>how we treat each other</em> in the failure. The wing's next play has to be an act of repair — a pass, a hustle, a high-five. That's how teams build IPR into team culture: the recovery is <strong>visible</strong>."
          ]
        },
        {
          key: 'D',
          text: 'Call both players over at the next break and talk through it.',
          verdict: 'IPR',
          verdictClass: 'ipr',
          verdictLabel: 'Right — as a follow-up, not a first move',
          analysis: [
            "Pulling them aside at the next break is the <em>right</em> conversation to have. Ask the wing: what were you feeling? Ask the center: what did you hear? Model the repair.",
            "Just don't skip option C first. The in-the-moment redirect is what keeps the whole team learning; the break-time conversation is what helps these two specific players grow. You want both."
          ],
          danielle: [
            "The conversation is where the learning sticks. But I want the <em>in-the-moment</em> redirect first, because <strong>every other player on the field is watching how I respond</strong>. The water-break chat is for them. The live cue is for everyone else."
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      id: 3,
      label: 'THE MOMENT',
      title: 'The silent shutdown',
      text: 'Your usually vocal midfielder has gone quiet. No stick slam. No frustration. Just — <em>absent</em>. She hasn\'t talked to a teammate in 10 minutes. She missed two easy passes and didn\'t react to either. <strong>Nothing looks wrong, but nothing is right.</strong>',
      timing: '▸ No clock on this one. This is the INR most coaches miss.',
      choices: [
        {
          key: 'A',
          text: 'Push her harder. High standards will snap her back.',
          verdict: 'INR',
          verdictClass: 'inr',
          verdictLabel: 'Mistakes the symptom for the problem',
          analysis: [
